Step 1 — Fix .pem File Permissions:
  Navigate to your EC2Tutorial1.pem file in File Explorer
  Right-click the file → Select Properties
  Go to the Security tab → Click Advanced
  Click Disable Inheritance → Select "Remove all inherited permissions from this object"
  Click Add → Select a principal → Type your Windows username (e.g., naresh) → Click OK
  Check Full Control → Click OK → Apply → OK

Step 2 — Connect to EC2 via PowerShell:
  Open PowerShell
  Navigate to the folder where your .pem file is located:
      ssh -i .\EC2Tutorial1.pem ec2-user@13.127.207.240

Step 3 — Result:
  If permissions are set correctly, this will successfully connect you to your EC2 instance 
  at IP address 13.127.207.240 via the terminal.

